        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 9:23PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 922 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Augusta Mall, or near Fort Eisenhower, moving southwest at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grovetown, Fort Eisenhower, Martinez, Hephzibah, Harlem, Glendale,
South Augusta, Summerville, Augusta Mall, Daniel Field, Village Plaza
Shopping Center, Midtown, Blythe, Keysville, Liberty Park Community
Center, Glenn Hills, Adamsville, Bath-Edie, Westover Memorial Park,
and Richmond County Recreation Center.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 20 in Georgia between mile markers 194 and 199.
Interstate 520 in Georgia between mile markers 1 and 9.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
